If the content is not a valid json, a `ValueError` will be thrown (and captured).

I don't know what the status code for this error is (we haven't captured it in the logs where we have seen the error). There is not a trivial way to reproduce the error. Yet, the error continues to happen, every once in a while. So, using content seems to be the only approach unless we have more information about the error (it is not documented in the databricks REST API).

