No, since the whitelist only applies at the top level.

```
whitelist = ['b']
default_config = {
    'a': 1,
    'b': { 'foob': 1, 'baz': 23}
    'c': { 'fooc': 2 }
}
new_config = {
    'b': { 'bar': 1 }
}
_deep_update(default_config, new_config, False, whitelist) == {'a': 1, 'b': { 'bar': 1 }, 'c': { 'fooc': 2 }}
new_config2 = {
    'c': { 'barc': 1 }
}
_deep_update(default_config, new_config2, False, whitelist) # throws an error
